#. <section class="sutta" id="an6.1"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an6.1:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 6"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 6"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.1:0.2"
msgid "1. Āhuneyyavagga"
msgstr "1. Worthy of Offerings"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an6.1:0.3"
msgid "1. Paṭhamaāhuneyyasutta"
msgstr "1. Worthy of Offerings (1st)"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.279"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
#. <span class="evam">
msgctxt "an6.1:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

#. </span>
msgctxt "an6.1:1.2"
msgid ""
"ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery."

msgctxt "an6.1:1.3"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants:"

msgctxt "an6.1:1.4"
msgid "“bhikkhavo”ti."
msgstr "“Mendicants!”"

msgctxt "an6.1:1.5"
msgid "“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Venerable sir,” they replied."

msgctxt "an6.1:1.6"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an6.1:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Chahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu āhuneyyo hoti pāhuneyyo "
"dakkhiṇeyyo añjalikaraṇīyo anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ lokassa."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, a mendicant with six factors is worthy of offerings dedicated "
"to the gods, worthy of hospitality, worthy of a religious donation, worthy "
"of veneration with joined palms, and is the supreme field of merit for the "
"world."

msgctxt "an6.1:2.2"
msgid "Katamehi chahi?"
msgstr "What six?"

msgctxt "an6.1:2.3"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu cakkhunā rūpaṃ disvā neva sumano hoti na dummano, "
"upekkhako viharati sato sampajāno."
msgstr ""
"It’s a mendicant who, when they see a sight with their eyes, is neither "
"happy nor sad. They remain equanimous, mindful and aware."

msgctxt "an6.1:2.4"
msgid "Sotena saddaṃ sutvā …"
msgstr "When they hear a sound with their ears …"

msgctxt "an6.1:2.5"
msgid "ghānena gandhaṃ ghāyitvā …"
msgstr "When they smell an odor with their nose …"

msgctxt "an6.1:2.6"
msgid "jivhāya rasaṃ sāyitvā …"
msgstr "When they taste a flavor with their tongue …"

msgctxt "an6.1:2.7"
msgid "kāyena phoṭṭhabbaṃ phusitvā …"
msgstr "When they feel a touch with their body …"

msgctxt "an6.1:2.8"
msgid ""
"manasā dhammaṃ viññāya neva sumano hoti na dummano, upekkhako viharati sato "
"sampajāno."
msgstr ""
"When they know a thought with their mind, they’re neither happy nor sad. "
"They remain equanimous, mindful and aware."

msgctxt "an6.1:2.9"
msgid ""
"Imehi kho, bhikkhave, chahi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu āhuneyyo hoti "
"pāhuneyyo dakkhiṇeyyo añjalikaraṇīyo anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ lokassā”ti."
msgstr ""
"A mendicant with these six factors is worthy of offerings dedicated to the "
"gods, worthy of hospitality, worthy of a religious donation, worthy of "
"veneration with joined palms, and is the supreme field of merit for the "
"world.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an6.1:3.1"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā."
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said."

msgctxt "an6.1:3.2"
msgid "Attamanā te bhikkhū bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandunti."
msgstr "Satisfied, the mendicants were happy with what the Buddha said."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an6.1:3.3"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
